import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='region', y='avg_income', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of average income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.ylabel('Average Income')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Regions', loc='upper right', labels=data['region'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data['group'].value_counts(normalize=True)
    ax = sns.barplot(x=group_counts.index, y=group_counts.values)
    ax.set(xlabel='Group', ylabel='Proportion')
    plt.title('What is the proportion of each group in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(group_counts.index, title='Groups', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
